[narrator]
<i>It was a perfect day</i>

25
00:00:58,708 --> 00:01:01,625
<i>in the country for a hike.</i>

26
00:01:01,708 --> 00:01:03,625
<i>♪♪</i>

27
00:01:03,708 --> 00:01:04,833
[both gasp]

28
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:07,000
Uh-oh.

29
00:01:07,083 --> 00:01:14,000
<i>♪♪</i>

30
00:01:14,083 --> 00:01:17,333
[narrator] <i>Some places in the</i>
<i>country were hard to reach.</i>

31
00:01:17,416 --> 00:01:20,333
[rhythmic music]

32
00:01:20,416 --> 00:01:23,833
<i>♪♪</i>

33
00:01:23,916 --> 00:01:25,541
Whoo!

34
00:01:25,625 --> 00:01:28,000
<i>♪♪</i>

35
00:01:28,083 --> 00:01:30,000
[narrator]
<i>But they were worth it.</i>

36
00:01:30,083 --> 00:01:33,000
[upbeat jazz piano music]

37
00:01:33,083 --> 00:01:37,083
<i>♪♪</i>

38
00:01:44,333 --> 00:01:45,583
Hmm.

39
00:01:45,666 --> 00:01:50,958
<i>♪♪</i>

40
00:01:51,041 --> 00:01:53,625
Pretty good hiking
for a city kid, George.

41
00:01:53,708 --> 00:01:56,541
Aww.

42
00:01:56,625 --> 00:01:58,041
We're almost there.

43
00:01:58,125 --> 00:02:00,375
The super-secret hidden,

44
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:02,958
nobody-but-us-knows-about-it
view!

45
00:02:03,041 --> 00:02:05,583
[giggles]

46
00:02:05,666 --> 00:02:06,958
Hey, I'm getting hungry!

47
00:02:07,041 --> 00:02:08,541
Sandwich break?

48
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:10,583
[chatters hungrily]

49
00:02:10,666 --> 00:02:15,583
<i>♪♪</i>

50
00:02:18,083 --> 00:02:19,583
Uh-oh!

51
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:25,833
Whoa! Ow!

52
00:02:25,916 --> 00:02:27,916
[grunts]

53
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,750
[grunting worriedly]

54
00:02:29,833 --> 00:02:31,750
I'm all right! I'm all right!

55
00:02:31,833 --> 00:02:33,708
[groans] Ow!

56
00:02:35,041 --> 00:02:37,041
I guess I'm not all right.

57
00:02:37,125 --> 00:02:39,541
[whimpering]

58
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:41,833
I don't think I can walk
on my leg, George.

59
00:02:41,916 --> 00:02:43,041
Aww...

60
00:02:43,125 --> 00:02:45,083
Maybe if I go slow.

61
00:02:45,166 --> 00:02:48,375
[chatters encouragingly]

62
00:02:48,458 --> 00:02:50,708
Ouch!

63
00:02:50,791 --> 00:02:52,041
That's not going to work.

64
00:02:52,125 --> 00:02:54,000
[chatters nervously]

65
00:02:54,083 --> 00:02:56,625
[narrator] <i>George knew</i>
<i>he needed to go for help.</i>

66
00:02:56,708 --> 00:02:58,666
[chatters soothingly]

67
00:02:58,750 --> 00:03:03,458
<i>♪♪</i>

68
00:03:05,541 --> 00:03:08,083
Hey, thanks
for the lift, guys.

69
00:03:13,125 --> 00:03:16,458
You did a great job getting
help for your friend, George.

70
00:03:16,541 --> 00:03:18,375
[chatters happily]

71
00:03:18,458 --> 00:03:19,750
I called your mom, Bill.

72
00:03:19,833 --> 00:03:21,583
She's gonna meet you
at the hospital.

73
00:03:21,666 --> 00:03:24,083
You know, I'm actually
looking forward to going there.

74
00:03:24,166 --> 00:03:25,916
-You are?
-[chatters]

75
00:03:26,000 --> 00:03:28,875
Yeah! They have the best
fruit cup I've ever tasted.

76
00:03:28,958 --> 00:03:31,458
It almost makes
all this worth it.

77
00:03:31,541 --> 00:03:33,625
[chatters happily]

78
00:03:33,708 --> 00:03:35,875
Hey, George,
would you like to ride

79
00:03:35,958 --> 00:03:37,041
in the ambulance with us?

80
00:03:37,125 --> 00:03:40,791
[chatters happily]

81
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:42,750
Sure. Why not?

82
00:03:42,833 --> 00:03:44,916
[upbeat jazzy music]

83
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:47,916
[siren wailing]

84
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,958
<i>♪♪</i>

85
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:51,958
[chatters curiously]

86
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:54,125
It's the paramedic's job
to give people first aid

87
00:03:54,208 --> 00:03:55,791
and bring them
to the hospital, George.

88
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:57,541
[chatters happily]

89
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:59,083
Right.

90
00:03:59,166 --> 00:04:01,041
And the ambulance
has all the equipment

91
00:04:01,125 --> 00:04:02,291
we need.

92
00:04:02,375 --> 00:04:04,250
It's almost like
a rolling hospital.

93
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:06,416
Oh!

94
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:09,875
<i>♪♪</i>

95
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:12,875
[clatters]

96
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:19,625
<i>♪♪</i>

97
00:04:19,708 --> 00:04:22,166
Hey, Danny. Hey, Nurse Paula.

98
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:24,083
How's it going, Barry?

99
00:04:24,166 --> 00:04:26,166
Hi, Trish!

100
00:04:26,250 --> 00:04:29,541
Wow, you seem to know
a lot of people here.

101
00:04:29,625 --> 00:04:32,541
Yeah, I've been
in the hospital before.

102
00:04:32,625 --> 00:04:33,958
[chatters in confusion]

103
00:04:34,041 --> 00:04:36,541
Oh, yeah,
broke my arm playing chess.

104
00:04:36,625 --> 00:04:37,708
Met everybody.

105
00:04:37,791 --> 00:04:39,625
Well, hello, Bill.

106
00:04:39,708 --> 00:04:41,041
What happened?

107
00:04:41,125 --> 00:04:42,666
Hurt my leg.

108
00:04:42,750 --> 00:04:44,083
What was it this time?

109
00:04:44,166 --> 00:04:45,666
Checkers?

110
00:04:45,750 --> 00:04:48,541
Turkey sandwich.

111
00:04:48,625 --> 00:04:50,666
[chatters curiously]

112
00:04:50,750 --> 00:04:52,708
It's a wristband
for the doctors and nurses

113
00:04:52,791 --> 00:04:54,625
to keep track
of all of us patients.

114
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:56,625
Oh!

115
00:04:56,708 --> 00:05:00,208
<i>♪♪</i>

116
00:05:00,291 --> 00:05:01,875
Well, Bill,
it looks like your leg

117
00:05:01,958 --> 00:05:03,750
is broken in three places.

118
00:05:03,833 --> 00:05:05,041
Really?

119
00:05:05,125 --> 00:05:07,708
[chatters curiously]

120
00:05:07,791 --> 00:05:10,875
[narrator] <i>Bill's leg looked</i>
<i>like it was all in one piece.</i>

121
00:05:10,958 --> 00:05:12,458
[laughs]

122
00:05:12,541 --> 00:05:14,125
You can't see the break
on the outside.

123
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:16,833
That's why we radiologists
use an x-ray machine.

124
00:05:16,916 --> 00:05:19,208
It takes pictures of how you
look on the inside.

125
00:05:19,291 --> 00:05:21,208
[chatters happily]

126
00:05:21,291 --> 00:05:23,583
[narrator] <i>George had seen</i>
<i>an x-ray before.</i>

127
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:26,208
[counts to three]

128
00:05:26,291 --> 00:05:28,125
That's right,
there are fractures

129
00:05:28,208 --> 00:05:31,500
here, here, and here.

130
00:05:31,583 --> 00:05:32,916
What happened?

131
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,541
Slipped on a turkey sandwich.

132
00:05:35,625 --> 00:05:38,166
Of course.
I should've guessed.

133
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:40,583
[chatters thoughtfully]

134
00:05:40,666 --> 00:05:42,208
[narrator] <i>George</i>
<i>thought he'd like to have</i>

135
00:05:42,291 --> 00:05:44,000
<i>an x-ray machine of his own.</i>

136
00:05:44,083 --> 00:05:47,541
[chattering wistfully]

137
00:05:47,625 --> 00:05:49,083
Looks like Bill's
gonna need a cast

138
00:05:49,166 --> 00:05:51,250
so his leg can heal.

139
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:53,833
We make a cast
by wrapping your leg

140
00:05:53,916 --> 00:05:55,916
with lots of layers
so it can't move.

141
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:58,041
[bright piano music]

142
00:05:58,125 --> 00:06:00,875
That's strange.
Where's my...

143
00:06:00,958 --> 00:06:02,041
[gasps]

144
00:06:02,125 --> 00:06:05,125
[grunting spookily]

145
00:06:06,583 --> 00:06:08,250
[laughs]

146
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:11,791
[both laughing]

147
00:06:11,875 --> 00:06:14,625
Thanks for lunch!

148
00:06:14,708 --> 00:06:18,125
Now, your job is to rest up
until your mom gets here.

149
00:06:18,208 --> 00:06:20,208
Enjoy your lunch.

150
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:22,041
Oh, I will!

151
00:06:22,125 --> 00:06:23,916
Yes!

152
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,708
Fruit cu--

153
00:06:25,791 --> 00:06:28,750
Grapes? Ugh.

154
00:06:28,833 --> 00:06:31,916
I was really looking
forward to that fruit cup.

155
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:33,791
I'd trade,
but I can't leave the bed.

156
00:06:33,875 --> 00:06:36,041
[chatters helpfully]

157
00:06:36,125 --> 00:06:39,166
[narrator] <i>Bill couldn't leave,</i>
<i>but George could.</i>

158
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:42,875
<i>♪♪</i>

159
00:06:42,958 --> 00:06:45,166
Huh?

160
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:47,958
[narrator] <i>George didn't think</i>
<i>food carts could disappear.</i>

161
00:06:48,041 --> 00:06:49,833
<i>But maybe they did.</i>

162
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:55,083
<i>♪♪</i>

163
00:06:55,166 --> 00:06:57,333
<i>A refrigerator!</i>

164
00:06:57,416 --> 00:07:00,291
<i>Maybe they kept the fruit cups</i>
<i>in there.</i>

165
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:04,166
Ahh! Ah-ha!

166
00:07:04,250 --> 00:07:06,666
<i>♪♪</i>

167
00:07:06,750 --> 00:07:09,041
Oh, hello, little monkey.

168
00:07:09,125 --> 00:07:10,833
Are you lost?

169
00:07:10,916 --> 00:07:13,833
[chatters in embarrassment]

170
00:07:13,916 --> 00:07:15,750
This is the lab.

171
00:07:15,833 --> 00:07:17,333
Oh!

172
00:07:17,416 --> 00:07:18,958
We help the doctors
figure out

173
00:07:19,041 --> 00:07:20,208
what's wrong with the patients.

174
00:07:20,291 --> 00:07:21,750
Hey, want to see?

175
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,250
[chatters happily]

176
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:27,250
<i>♪♪</i>

177
00:07:27,333 --> 00:07:29,041
Oh!

178
00:07:29,125 --> 00:07:30,625
I'm checking to see if

179
00:07:30,708 --> 00:07:32,333
this patient's blood cells
are healthy.

180
00:07:32,416 --> 00:07:35,041
[chatters happily]

181
00:07:35,125 --> 00:07:36,791
[gasps and chatters]

182
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:40,708
[chatters excitedly]

183
00:07:40,791 --> 00:07:43,375
Oh... Goodbye!

184
00:07:43,458 --> 00:07:45,208
Who were you talking to?

185
00:07:45,291 --> 00:07:47,041
A monkey.

186
00:07:47,125 --> 00:07:48,875
Oh.

187
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:53,791
[upbeat jazz music]

188
00:07:53,875 --> 00:07:56,708
<i>♪♪</i>

189
00:07:56,791 --> 00:08:00,166
[chatters curiously]

190
00:08:00,250 --> 00:08:01,916
[narrator] <i>There was a sink.</i>

191
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:05,083
<i>George hoped a kitchen</i>
<i>with fruit cups was nearby.</i>

192
00:08:05,166 --> 00:08:08,291
[gasps and chatters happily]

193
00:08:08,375 --> 00:08:11,750
Sorry, only doctors
can come in here.

194
00:08:11,833 --> 00:08:13,125
[chatters curiously]

195
00:08:13,208 --> 00:08:15,166
This is the operating room,

196
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:18,083
where we perform
operations on patients.

197
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:20,083
[chatters in confusion]

198
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:22,833
Oh, well, when a person has
something wrong

199
00:08:22,916 --> 00:08:24,958
with their body
that needs some--

200
00:08:25,041 --> 00:08:26,041
[chatters excitedly]

201
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:27,750
Huh?

202
00:08:27,833 --> 00:08:30,083
<i>♪♪</i>

203
00:08:30,166 --> 00:08:31,416
[narrator] <i>Another cart!</i>

204
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:33,416
<i>Maybe it had the lunch.</i>

205
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,875
[chatters in disappointment]

206
00:08:35,957 --> 00:08:37,791
[narrator] <i>Nope, only laundry.</i>

207
00:08:37,875 --> 00:08:41,875
<i>♪♪</i>

208
00:08:41,957 --> 00:08:43,082
Oh...

209
00:08:43,166 --> 00:08:44,833
A-ha!

210
00:08:44,916 --> 00:08:47,416
[narrator] <i>This must be where</i>
<i>they kept the fruit cups.</i>

211
00:08:47,500 --> 00:08:49,958
<i>♪♪</i>

212
00:08:50,041 --> 00:08:53,083
I brought a funny book
to read you today!

213
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,291
[children cheering]

214
00:08:55,375 --> 00:08:57,041
And who do we have here?

215
00:08:57,125 --> 00:09:00,125
[chattering happily]

216
00:09:00,208 --> 00:09:03,125
[laughter and applause]

217
00:09:03,208 --> 00:09:05,458
Hey, my name's Jesse.

218
00:09:05,541 --> 00:09:07,333
I lead story time
for these children

219
00:09:07,416 --> 00:09:08,916
who are staying
in the hospital.

220
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:10,791
Would you like to stay
and hear a story?

221
00:09:10,875 --> 00:09:14,208
[chattering conversationally]

222
00:09:14,291 --> 00:09:16,375
[all] Bye-bye.

223
00:09:16,458 --> 00:09:19,041
[narrator]<i> Unfortunately,</i>
<i>George couldn't stay.</i>

224
00:09:19,125 --> 00:09:21,166
<i>He was on an important mission.</i>

225
00:09:21,250 --> 00:09:22,916
<i>♪♪</i>

226
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,958
Hello!

227
00:09:25,041 --> 00:09:28,208
[narrator] <i>George wondered</i>
<i>who that man was talking to.</i>

228
00:09:28,291 --> 00:09:30,500
[chatters inquisitively]

229
00:09:30,583 --> 00:09:33,458
Do you want to see
my son in the nursery?

230
00:09:33,541 --> 00:09:35,375
Uh-huh.

231
00:09:35,458 --> 00:09:37,000
Ooh.

232
00:09:37,083 --> 00:09:39,833
[chatters happily]

233
00:09:39,916 --> 00:09:41,166
Want to say hi?

234
00:09:41,250 --> 00:09:43,958
[chatters happily]

235
00:09:44,041 --> 00:09:47,125
[sleepy music]

236
00:09:47,208 --> 00:09:48,333
Look at my son.

237
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:51,041
Isn't he adorable?

238
00:09:51,125 --> 00:09:52,416
Ah.

239
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:58,833
[chatters excitedly]

240
00:09:58,916 --> 00:10:04,750
<i>♪♪</i>

241
00:10:06,458 --> 00:10:08,875
[chatters happily]

242
00:10:08,958 --> 00:10:11,083
[narrator]
<i>George was in the cafeteria!</i>

243
00:10:11,166 --> 00:10:14,083
[triumphant music]

244
00:10:14,166 --> 00:10:15,875
<i>♪♪</i>

245
00:10:15,958 --> 00:10:17,541
A-ha!

246
00:10:17,625 --> 00:10:19,791
[chatters in confusion]

247
00:10:19,875 --> 00:10:21,375
Oh, hi there.

248
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:24,041
[chatters]

249
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:27,000
Mm.
Wish they had some grapes.

250
00:10:27,083 --> 00:10:30,000
[chatters excitedly]

251
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:33,000
[upbeat music]

252
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:35,541
<i>♪♪</i>

253
00:10:35,625 --> 00:10:37,458
[chatters happily]

254
00:10:37,541 --> 00:10:39,375
Oh, thanks!

255
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:41,875
[chatters happily]

256
00:10:41,958 --> 00:10:44,458
<i>♪♪</i>

257
00:10:44,541 --> 00:10:46,500
Oh, good! You're back!

258
00:10:46,583 --> 00:10:48,375
[chatters triumphantly]

259
00:10:48,458 --> 00:10:50,041
[giggles]

260
00:10:50,125 --> 00:10:51,333
Fruit cup?

261
00:10:51,416 --> 00:10:53,291
Whoa! You got it!

262
00:10:53,375 --> 00:10:54,916
Thanks, George.

263
00:10:55,000 --> 00:10:57,041
[chatters happily]

264
00:10:57,125 --> 00:10:58,916
<i>♪♪</i>

265
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:00,333
Ah...

266
00:11:00,416 --> 00:11:02,416
Just like I remember.

267
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:05,916
[narrator] <i>George was happy</i>
<i>he could help out his friend.</i>

268
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,833
-Want some?
-Ah!

269
00:11:07,916 --> 00:11:09,458
<i>♪♪</i>

270
00:11:09,541 --> 00:11:12,416
Mm-mm.

271
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:15,041
Check out my new wheelchair.

272
00:11:15,125 --> 00:11:16,291
The doctor says this is how

273
00:11:16,375 --> 00:11:18,083
I have to get around
for a few weeks.

274
00:11:18,166 --> 00:11:20,541
[chatters happily]

275
00:11:20,625 --> 00:11:22,208
My mom's on her way,

276
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:23,541
but do you want a ride
before she gets here?

277
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:25,083
[chatters happily]

278
00:11:25,166 --> 00:11:26,958
Well, climb aboard!

279
00:11:27,041 --> 00:11:30,208
[upbeat music]

280
00:11:30,291 --> 00:11:32,041
Whoa, George!

281
00:11:32,125 --> 00:11:35,041
[laughter]

282
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:40,875
<i>♪♪</i>

283
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:48,000
[narrator] <i>The next day was</i>
<i>a perfect day in the country</i>

284
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,625
to build a city.

285
00:11:49,708 --> 00:11:52,458
This was the biggest,
best block city

286
00:11:52,541 --> 00:11:54,250
George had ever built.

287
00:11:54,333 --> 00:11:55,583
It had roads,

288
00:11:55,666 --> 00:11:57,916
and ramps,

289
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:01,041
and bridges.

290
00:12:01,125 --> 00:12:04,375
[making car noises]

291
00:12:04,458 --> 00:12:07,083
[narrator]
<i>It even had a car wash.</i>

292
00:12:07,166 --> 00:12:08,458
[Bill] Yoo-hoo!

293
00:12:09,958 --> 00:12:11,416
[chatters happily]

294
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:13,250
[narrator] <i>Bill was back.</i>

295
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:15,208
Wanna sign my cast?

296
00:12:15,291 --> 00:12:17,458
[chatters happily]

297
00:12:17,541 --> 00:12:20,166
The doctor says I have to
wear it for a few more weeks.

298
00:12:20,250 --> 00:12:22,625
Check out the signatures
I've got so far.

299
00:12:22,708 --> 00:12:25,000
My cousin, my mom,

300
00:12:25,083 --> 00:12:28,125
and look!
One from my neighbor's dog.

301
00:12:28,208 --> 00:12:31,208
[chatters happily]

302
00:12:34,083 --> 00:12:37,208
Nice! Thanks, George!

303
00:12:37,291 --> 00:12:38,625
[chatters happily]

304
00:12:38,708 --> 00:12:42,041
Ooh! [chatters]

305
00:12:42,125 --> 00:12:44,916
Um... My delivery replacement

306
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:48,166
is coming to pick up the
newspapers soon, but...

307
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:50,166
I can come in for a minute.

308
00:12:50,250 --> 00:12:53,166
[chatters excitedly]

309
00:12:53,250 --> 00:12:54,583
Ta-da!

310
00:12:54,666 --> 00:12:56,541
Oh?

311
00:12:56,625 --> 00:12:57,958
Huh?

312
00:12:58,041 --> 00:13:00,416
Wheelchair means
I can't come in.

313
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:02,583
[chatters in disappointment]

314
00:13:02,666 --> 00:13:04,291
[narrator]
<i>What good was building a city</i>

315
00:13:04,375 --> 00:13:06,583
if you couldn't
show it to your friends?

316
00:13:06,666 --> 00:13:08,333
[chatters thoughtfully]

317
00:13:08,416 --> 00:13:11,250
[gentle piano music]

318
00:13:11,333 --> 00:13:14,708
<i>♪♪</i>

319
00:13:14,791 --> 00:13:17,333
Yeah!

320
00:13:17,416 --> 00:13:19,541
A-ha!

321
00:13:19,625 --> 00:13:21,458
[narrator]
<i>Maybe there was a way.</i>

322
00:13:21,541 --> 00:13:28,541
<i>♪♪</i>

323
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:34,750
[chatters happily]

324
00:13:34,833 --> 00:13:38,041
Hey, a ramp!

325
00:13:38,125 --> 00:13:41,750
That is a particularly
good idea for a city kid.

326
00:13:41,833 --> 00:13:44,291
<i>♪♪</i>

327
00:13:44,375 --> 00:13:46,458
Whoa!

328
00:13:46,541 --> 00:13:49,333
[narrator] <i>Bill's weight made</i>
<i>the ramp bend in the middle.</i>

329
00:13:49,416 --> 00:13:51,666
<i>They needed a way</i>
<i>to make it stronger.</i>

330
00:13:51,750 --> 00:13:55,416
[upbeat music]

331
00:13:55,500 --> 00:13:57,166
Good idea!

332
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,666
[Carla] Excuse me!

333
00:13:58,750 --> 00:14:01,125
Whoa!

334
00:14:01,208 --> 00:14:02,583
Are you Bill?

335
00:14:02,666 --> 00:14:04,208
That's me!

336
00:14:04,291 --> 00:14:05,333
Carla.

337
00:14:05,416 --> 00:14:06,625
And this is George.

338
00:14:06,708 --> 00:14:08,291
[chatters happily]

339
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:10,541
Nice to meet you, George.

340
00:14:10,625 --> 00:14:12,375
So where are those newspapers

341
00:14:12,458 --> 00:14:13,708
you need delivered?

342
00:14:13,791 --> 00:14:16,791
Uh, wait, uh...

343
00:14:16,875 --> 00:14:19,125
You're the newspaper deliverer

344
00:14:19,208 --> 00:14:20,458
who just moved to town?

345
00:14:20,541 --> 00:14:22,791
You're looking at her.

346
00:14:22,875 --> 00:14:25,083
You hurt your leg too?

347
00:14:25,166 --> 00:14:26,166
Nope!

348
00:14:26,250 --> 00:14:27,750
I've always used a wheelchair.

349
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,458
This is how I get around.

350
00:14:29,541 --> 00:14:31,791
[giggles] Woohoo!

351
00:14:31,875 --> 00:14:33,458
Wow!

352
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:35,458
[chatters in surprise]

353
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:39,083
Anyway, I'm happy
to take over your route.

354
00:14:39,166 --> 00:14:40,458
What's the matter?

355
00:14:40,541 --> 00:14:41,750
Are you sick?

356
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,791
Oh... No!

357
00:14:43,875 --> 00:14:47,083
Uh, that is...

358
00:14:47,166 --> 00:14:49,625
I was worried about getting
my whole route done

359
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:53,791
in time in a wheelchair.

360
00:14:53,875 --> 00:14:56,125
Oh. In that case,

361
00:14:56,208 --> 00:14:57,666
why don't we each take half?

362
00:14:57,750 --> 00:14:59,250
That way, we'll do the job

363
00:14:59,333 --> 00:15:00,666
twice as fast.

364
00:15:00,750 --> 00:15:02,583
Sure!

365
00:15:02,666 --> 00:15:03,708
Wanna come along?

366
00:15:03,791 --> 00:15:06,166
Uh-huh!

367
00:15:06,250 --> 00:15:09,166
[upbeat piano music]

368
00:15:09,250 --> 00:15:13,791
<i>♪♪</i>

369
00:15:13,875 --> 00:15:16,291
Whoa! Nice form!

370
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:18,500
Perfect accuracy!

371
00:15:18,583 --> 00:15:21,208
Not bad, not bad at all.

372
00:15:21,291 --> 00:15:23,125
Okay, my turn.

373
00:15:23,208 --> 00:15:24,208
[grunts]

374
00:15:26,375 --> 00:15:29,666
Uh... I gotta get used
to this chair.

375
00:15:29,750 --> 00:15:33,458
[chatters helpfully]

376
00:15:33,541 --> 00:15:35,416
Thanks, George!

377
00:15:36,666 --> 00:15:38,541
[grunts]

378
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:41,333
And that's the last one!

379
00:15:41,416 --> 00:15:43,583
We did it!

380
00:15:43,666 --> 00:15:46,666
[chatters happily]

381
00:15:48,166 --> 00:15:49,750
We're going over
to George's house

382
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:51,250
to see his block city.

383
00:15:51,333 --> 00:15:52,375
Wanna come?

384
00:15:52,458 --> 00:15:54,708
Sure! Sounds like fun!

385
00:15:54,791 --> 00:15:57,708
[rock and roll music]

386
00:15:57,791 --> 00:16:00,875
<i>♪♪</i>

387
00:16:00,958 --> 00:16:04,583
[panting]

388
00:16:04,666 --> 00:16:07,125
Whoa, nice ramp!

389
00:16:09,791 --> 00:16:12,250
[imitating car noises]

390
00:16:12,333 --> 00:16:14,791
Best block city
I've ever seen.

391
00:16:14,875 --> 00:16:16,541
George is a city kid,

392
00:16:16,625 --> 00:16:19,708
knows everything there
is to know about cities.

393
00:16:20,916 --> 00:16:22,416
What's that?

394
00:16:22,500 --> 00:16:25,541
[gentle piano music]

395
00:16:25,625 --> 00:16:29,333
[chatters happily]

396
00:16:29,416 --> 00:16:31,708
We've got a real
bowling alley in town.

397
00:16:31,791 --> 00:16:33,541
We can take you there.

398
00:16:33,625 --> 00:16:35,791
We know all the best spots
around here, right, George?

399
00:16:35,875 --> 00:16:37,416
Ah!

400
00:16:37,500 --> 00:16:39,583
Like where to pick
wild berries,

401
00:16:39,666 --> 00:16:41,708
and a really cool cave.

402
00:16:41,791 --> 00:16:44,541
Oh! And there's
a super secret...

403
00:16:44,625 --> 00:16:46,750
[whispers]
middle of the woods pond.

404
00:16:46,833 --> 00:16:49,458
Shh!

405
00:16:49,541 --> 00:16:53,708
[whispers] A super secret
middle of the woods pond?

406
00:16:53,791 --> 00:16:55,291
Yeah!

407
00:16:55,375 --> 00:16:58,500
It's one of the best places
I've ever--

408
00:17:01,333 --> 00:17:03,416
Actually, never mind.

409
00:17:03,500 --> 00:17:04,790
It's not that great.

410
00:17:04,875 --> 00:17:06,290
Huh?

411
00:17:06,375 --> 00:17:08,458
Sounds great to me!

412
00:17:08,540 --> 00:17:09,583
Yeah.

413
00:17:09,665 --> 00:17:11,250
But it's a long hike,

414
00:17:11,333 --> 00:17:13,415
and I broke my leg
just trying to walk there.

415
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:14,790
I'm up for the challenge.

416
00:17:14,875 --> 00:17:16,540
Where is it?

417
00:17:16,625 --> 00:17:18,625
It's way deep in the woods!

418
00:17:18,708 --> 00:17:20,833
You have to get past
a bunch of thorn bushes.

419
00:17:20,915 --> 00:17:23,375
Then there's a tree
across the path.

420
00:17:23,458 --> 00:17:25,708
I don't think we could
get there in wheelchairs.

421
00:17:25,790 --> 00:17:29,625
Well, we won't,
unless we try.

422
00:17:29,708 --> 00:17:31,458
[chatters encouragingly]

423
00:17:31,541 --> 00:17:34,291
I wish we could see all
the things we'll have to cross.

424
00:17:34,375 --> 00:17:37,625
[gentle piano music]

425
00:17:37,708 --> 00:17:39,666
Ah...

426
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:44,750
<i>♪♪</i>

427
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:49,666
Uh-huh... [giggles]

428
00:17:49,750 --> 00:17:52,000
Good idea, George!

429
00:17:52,083 --> 00:17:53,916
This is the log
we'll have to get over.

430
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:56,333
And there's the thorn bush
we'll have to pass.

431
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:59,875
Great! Now let's make a plan
to get through the woods.

432
00:17:59,958 --> 00:18:01,250
Okay.

433
00:18:01,333 --> 00:18:06,291
So how do we get over the log?

434
00:18:06,375 --> 00:18:09,000
[chatters thoughtfully]

435
00:18:09,083 --> 00:18:10,416
Ah!

436
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:15,833
Ah!

437
00:18:15,916 --> 00:18:18,875
But there's no ramp
in the woods.

438
00:18:18,958 --> 00:18:21,958
[chatters disappointedly]

439
00:18:23,291 --> 00:18:24,833
We can bring one.

440
00:18:24,916 --> 00:18:27,750
[chatters happily]

441
00:18:27,833 --> 00:18:30,750
Now, how are we going
to deal with that thorn bush?

442
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:34,291
Hmm...

443
00:18:34,375 --> 00:18:36,958
[upbeat piano music]

444
00:18:37,041 --> 00:18:39,708
Hard-packed trail
makes it easy!

445
00:18:39,791 --> 00:18:41,375
Just you wait!

446
00:18:41,458 --> 00:18:44,541
It gets a lot harder,
believe me.

447
00:18:44,625 --> 00:18:47,791
<i>♪♪</i>

448
00:18:47,875 --> 00:18:50,833
These are thorn bushes
I told you about.

449
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,333
[upbeat piano music]

450
00:18:54,416 --> 00:18:56,416
[chatters happily]

451
00:18:56,500 --> 00:18:58,416
Okay, if you really
think it'll work.

452
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:00,625
[chatters reassuringly]

453
00:19:00,708 --> 00:19:04,333
<i>♪♪</i>

454
00:19:04,416 --> 00:19:06,541
Hey, what do you know?
It worked!

455
00:19:06,625 --> 00:19:10,583
<i>♪♪</i>

456
00:19:10,666 --> 00:19:12,541
[grunting]

457
00:19:12,625 --> 00:19:15,041
[all cheering]

458
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:18,083
[cheerful piano music]

459
00:19:20,708 --> 00:19:24,708
<i>♪♪</i>

460
00:19:32,666 --> 00:19:34,333
[giggles]

461
00:19:36,541 --> 00:19:39,583
[laughing]

462
00:19:39,666 --> 00:19:43,541
Huh. The rain must have
created a creek.

463
00:19:45,583 --> 00:19:47,458
Ah!

464
00:19:47,541 --> 00:19:49,916
[cheerful piano music]

465
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,916
[chattering helpfully]

466
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:58,458
<i>♪♪</i>

467
00:19:58,541 --> 00:20:00,041
Good idea, George!

468
00:20:00,125 --> 00:20:02,041
[chattering helpfully]

469
00:20:02,125 --> 00:20:03,791
Okay, um...

470
00:20:03,875 --> 00:20:05,958
[stammering]
Well...

471
00:20:06,041 --> 00:20:08,625
Here goes nothing!

472
00:20:10,416 --> 00:20:15,041
<i>♪♪</i>

473
00:20:15,125 --> 00:20:19,666
Crossing... Crossing...

474
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:21,541
Ha! I made it!

475
00:20:21,625 --> 00:20:22,708
[all laughing]

476
00:20:22,791 --> 00:20:25,125
All right!

477
00:20:25,208 --> 00:20:28,416
[squelching]

478
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:31,083
Oh, no!

479
00:20:31,166 --> 00:20:33,666
Ugh. Mud.

480
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:35,625
Too sticky for our wheels.

481
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:38,708
[chatters in disappointment]

482
00:20:40,458 --> 00:20:42,666
Guess you were right
after all, Bill.

483
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:46,541
[sad piano music]

484
00:20:46,625 --> 00:20:50,416
It sure was nice up 'till now,
though.

485
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:51,666
Wait!

486
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:54,416
You're not--
You can't turn back!

487
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,750
We're almost there!

488
00:20:55,833 --> 00:20:58,916
But we don't have a way
to get across.

489
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,916
Ooh! Hey!

490
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,916
[upbeat piano music]

491
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:10,166
<i>♪♪</i>

492
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:12,125
[chatters excitedly]

493
00:21:15,625 --> 00:21:16,875
But...

494
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:19,041
[chatters helpfully]

495
00:21:19,125 --> 00:21:20,875
Okay!

496
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:23,541
<i>♪♪</i>

497
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:25,041
This is working!

498
00:21:25,125 --> 00:21:27,583
So let's figure out
how to get more boards.

499
00:21:27,666 --> 00:21:30,791
[chatters happily]

500
00:21:30,875 --> 00:21:36,541
<i>♪♪</i>

501
00:21:36,625 --> 00:21:38,500
Good thinking!

502
00:21:40,125 --> 00:21:42,208
Nice going, George!

503
00:21:42,291 --> 00:21:46,083
<i>♪♪</i>

504
00:21:46,166 --> 00:21:48,000
-Great job!
-We did it!

505
00:21:48,083 --> 00:21:50,125
I told you we could do it!

506
00:21:50,208 --> 00:21:51,875
Come on!

507
00:21:51,958 --> 00:21:54,916
[cheerful piano music]

508
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,125
<i>♪♪</i>

509
00:21:57,208 --> 00:21:58,916
You ready?

510
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,250
You bet!

511
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:06,958
<i>♪♪</i>

512
00:22:07,041 --> 00:22:09,666
Wow!

513
00:22:09,750 --> 00:22:12,666
[majestic music]

514
00:22:12,750 --> 00:22:14,875
<i>♪♪</i>

515
00:22:14,958 --> 00:22:20,125
The super secret
middle of the woods pond!

516
00:22:20,208 --> 00:22:22,250
[frog croaks]

517
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:24,916
<i>♪♪</i>

518
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,125
[croaking together]

519
00:22:27,208 --> 00:22:28,916
[giggling]

520
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:30,791
Wow!

521
00:22:30,875 --> 00:22:31,791
I must be the only kid
who's ever

522
00:22:31,875 --> 00:22:33,083
gotten his cast signed

523
00:22:33,166 --> 00:22:35,958
by a dog, a city kid,

524
00:22:36,083 --> 00:22:37,916
and a frog!

525
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:40,125
[all laughing]

526
00:22:40,208 --> 00:22:42,583
Hey, you know
what the best part

527
00:22:42,666 --> 00:22:45,708
of this super secret
middle of the woods pond is?

528
00:22:47,208 --> 00:22:49,750
Getting to share it
with friends!

529
00:22:49,833 --> 00:22:51,958
<i>♪♪</i>

530
00:22:52,041 --> 00:22:54,208
[all oohing and aahing]

531
00:22:54,291 --> 00:22:57,541
<i>♪♪</i>

